Students from non-English speaking countries must submit an official score report from one of the following testing agencies: TOEFL Internet-based test (iBT) score of 79, IELTS score of 6.0, PTE Academic score of 54, Duolingo score of 110, or successful completion of ELS Language Center's level 112. Test scores must be less than two years old.

International students must satisfy the UNA requirements for international student admission, including English proficiency. One of the following official scores is required: TOEFL iBT: 79, IELTS: 6.0, PTE: 54, or Duolingo: 110.

All applicants whose native language is not English are required to submit proof of English proficiency. This can be met by providing an official score report for one of the following: TOEFL with a minimum score of 79 on the iBT (internet-based test) or 550 on the PBT (paper-based test); IELTS with a minimum score of 6.0; PTE with a minimum score of 54; Duolingo with a minimum score of 105; or successful completion of Level 112 of the English Language Services (ELS) intensive program.

The University of Houston requires official, passing TOEFL or IELTS or Duolingo English Test (DET) scores for all applicants who are not U.S. citizens or U.S. permanent residents, unless they have earned a bachelor's or master's degree from a U.S. institution or from a country where English is the official language.

Evidence of English proficiency is required for all non-native English speaking applicants. Applicants must meet one of the following requirements: Test of English as a Foreign Language (TOEFL) Internet-Based Test (IBT) with a score of 79. International English Language Testing System (IELTS) with a score of 6.0. Pearson Test of English Academic (PTE) with a score of 54. Duolingo English Test with a score of 100. Completion of English Language Services (ELS) Level 112.
